  "texts": [
    "In this context, results vary considerably based on the technique or sample used, with accuracies from 65 to 80% [18,21,[23][24][25].",
    "In contrast, very few authors have focused on addressing the relationship between SS and other aspects of the disease [26,27].",
    "For example, the investigation of the connection between SS and neuropsychological impairment has received limited attention [10,28].",
    "This relevant aspect is not widely available since demonstrating that SS can be a reliable proxy for an individual's cognition requires its evaluation against standardized neuropsychological measures.",
    "However, most research has only utilized the Mini-Mental State Examination (MMSE) to explore the association of SS with cognitive status [29][30][31], typically within the context of the ADReSS challenge [32]."
